The paper deals with the modeling and analysis of HetNets, which are wireless networks with multiple types of base stations. This topic falls under the broad category of wireless communication networks, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category because the paper deals with the analysis of coverage probability and throughput, which are key performance metrics in wireless communication systems. Information theory is concerned with the fundamental limits of communication systems and the optimal use of resources to achieve these limits. 

cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a likely sub-category because the paper deals with the modeling and analysis of wireless networks, which are a subset of computer networks. Networking and Internet Architecture covers a wide range of topics related to the design, implementation, and analysis of computer networks. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible sub-category because the paper deals with the correlation between the locations of users and base stations, which can be seen as a form of social network. Social and Information Networks covers topics related to the analysis of social networks and the use of network analysis techniques in other domains.
